(60569, 'Marco Aurélio Tanaka', 'Galera fui começar a testar o Vagrant, e estou com um problema acho que com a VirtualBox. Tenho pouca experiência com linux. Sei o básico para desenvolvimento e tal. Mas nunca tive que recompilar um kernel. Vou ter que fazer isso? Segue os dados do meu terminal:\n\nlelotnk@lelotnk-acer:/vagrant$ vagrant up\nVirtualBox is complaining that the kernel module is not loaded. Please\nrun `VBoxManage --version` or open the VirtualBox GUI to see the error\nmessage which should contain instructions on how to fix this error.\nlelotnk@lelotnk-acer:/vagrant$ VBoxManage --version\nWARNING: The vboxdrv kernel module is not loaded. Either there is no module\n         available for the current kernel (3.8.0-26-generic) or it failed to\n         load. Please recompile the kernel module and install it by\n\n           sudo /etc/init.d/vboxdrv setup\n\n         You will not be able to start VMs until this problem is fixed.\n4.2.16r86992', '14811750159_10153122247605160', '2013-07-20 22:20:56'),
